  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 2.6,
      "end": 8.18,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 8.18,
      "end": 11.76,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit librivox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.16,
      "end": 21.3,
      "text": "The Ass and the Laptop and Aesop's Fable. There was once a man who had an ass and a",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 21.3,
      "end": 26.2,
      "text": "laptop. The ass was housed in the stable with plenty of oats and hay to eat, and was as",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 26.36,
      "end": 32.68,
      "text": "well off as an ass could be. The little dog was made a great pet of by his master, who",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 32.68,
      "end": 37.14,
      "text": "fondled him and often let him lie in his lap. And if he went out to dinner, he would bring",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 37.14,
      "end": 41.04,
      "text": "back a tidbit or two to give him when he ran to meet him on his return.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 43.14,
      "end": 49.02,
      "text": "The Ass had, it is true, a good deal of work to do, carting or grinding the corn, or carrying",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 49.02,
      "end": 54.98,
      "text": "the burdens of the farm. And air long he became very jealous, contrasting his own life of",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 54.98,
      "end": 57.8,
      "text": "labor with the ease and idleness of the lap-dog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 60.78,
      "end": 65.96,
      "text": "At last one day he broke his halter, and, frisking into the house just as his master sat down",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 65.96,
      "end": 71.26,
      "text": "to dinner, he pranced and capored about, mimicking the frolics of the little favorite, upsetting",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 71.26,
      "end": 78.2,
      "text": "the table and smashing the crockery with his clumsy efforts. Not content with that, he even",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 78.2,
      "end": 82.52,
      "text": "tried to jump on his master's lap, as he had often seen the dog allowed to do.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 83.82,
      "end": 89.62,
      "text": "At that, the servants, seeing the danger their master was in, belavored the silly ass with",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 89.62,
      "end": 93.94,
      "text": "sticks and cudules, and drove him back to his stable, half-dead with his beating.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 95.5,
      "end": 101.74,
      "text": "Alas, he cried, all this I have brought on myself. Why could I not be satisfied with my",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 101.74,
      "end": 106.98,
      "text": "natural and honorable position without wishing to imitate the ridiculous antics of that useless,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 106.98,
      "end": 108.1,
      "text": "little lap-dog?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 112.2,
      "end": 117.46,
      "text": "This has been an audio recording of the ass and the lap-dog from ASOP's Fables, read by",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 117.46,
      "end": 121.1,
      "text": "Andy Fluke of 13penny's.net for LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
